metadata.name: Circumscript #5
metadata.description:
It has always been a goal of mine to incorporate the worlds of physical and digital art together in a piece. And with circumscript I am the closest I've ever been. Circumscript uses a custom shader written to mix and "dilute" the colors on the canvas, thus creating a very physical feeling piece.

This dilution can be more or less depending on the edition, but always plays a huge role in the feel of the piece.


Happy new year.


----


[m] or [double tap] : opens the export/settings menu, use this menu to change the resolution, and make sure to press the reload button if you do.
[holding down] : zooms in on a certain area of the piece, depending on where your mouse/finger is. Use this feature to expore the complex textures of the piece in more detail, it's highly recommended to do this on a higher resolution setting.

The outputs can vary slighty per device, as there's a slight difference in how certain math gets interpreted on different devices with shaders.


----


Made with p5.js and webgl by Wouter Missler in 2022/3.

metadata.name: Hidden Intersections #67
metadata.description:
In this piece, two grids overlap:

1. a perfect one composed of lines drawn on the screen
2. an irregular one composed of linear zones that reference other parts of the screen

Everything you see in the final composition is a result of the overlapping intersections of these two grids with each other, and eventually themselves.


------------

Created as part of #genuaryTogether for #genuary2023, for the 4th day, theme: "intersections".

source code: https://github.com/protozoo/genuary23_04_intersections

controls:
- "s" key: save a png of the display
- "w" key: generate and save a 4k widescreen version of your seed (it will look different, but always be the same)

metadata.name: Hyper Pixel #178
metadata.description:
Somewhere between pixel-art and axonometric architectural projections, spatial compositions assembled from multi-resolution pixel precise fragments. 

Hyper Pixel is the result of a continued interest in using projections to represent three dimensional object in  two dimensional picture image, and embracing the fact that all digital images are two dimensional arrays of discrete pixels. In that sense it is also a reaction against both skeuomorphism, or mimicking older media in digital form, and the push towards ever increasing fidelity and resolution. The project uses Military perspective, a form of oblique projection, or 45° - 45° axonometric projection, because these angels can approximated fittingly by square pixel grid. 

Press s, m, l, x for exporting an image with increasing resolution.
Press p for pause.
Press r for refresh.

Made with P5.js by @introspect0r

metadata.name: NESTED IDENTITIES #186
metadata.description:
Nested identities redact fingerprints but deeper meaning can still be found.

Nested identifies refers to the idea that a person may have multiple identities that are interconnected and interdependent. These identities may be related to a person's cultural background, ethnicity, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, social class, profession, and other factors. It is possible that a person may want to conceal or redact certain aspects of their identity in order to protect their privacy or to avoid discrimination or persecution. However, even if certain details about a person's identity are hidden or redacted, it may still be possible to infer deeper meaning or understand more about their experiences and perspectives based on the context in which they express themselves and the information that is available.


The concept of nested identities highlights the complexity and multifaceted nature of a person's identity, and how different aspects of identity can intersect and influence each other. It is important to recognize and respect the diversity of identities that people may hold, and to be mindful of the ways in which power dynamics and social context can shape how people present and express their identities. It is also important to recognize that people's identities may evolve and change over time, and that everyone has the right to self-identify and to define their own identity on their own terms.

Press p to download a high quality export.

metadata.name: Emergence #16
metadata.description:
Emergent behaviour from a simple set of rules is what gives the universe all of its beauty and complexity.

In this project I have tried to capture some of this beauty in a study of simplicity leading to complex shapes and forms.

Watch as order slowly emerges from the chaos and interesting structures begin to form as the animation progresses.

metadata.name: MOUNTAINS #56
metadata.description:
"MOUNTAINS" is a work that belongs to the "FLUX Series", which utilizes the same techniques and processes as the previous work "FLUX". The shape in this piece is created by placing elements using noise and then performing recursive pixel operations on these elements.

The inspiration behind this work came from my continued sketches and studies of Flow Field, which led me to discover an expression of objects that seemed to be corroding. I believed that by applying this technique, I could create a realistic and vivid sculpture from a geometric shape.In this work, this corrosion treatment is applied to a geometric triangular shape of overlapping rectangles to form a realistic and dynamic mountain landscape.
It was as if geometric figures like Plato's "ideas" were materialized in the real world.

Additionally,  I was also inspired by the mountain views from my hometown at New Year's and by the manga background paintings of Yoshiharu Tsuge, who specializes in depicting villages with old hot springs.

It is possible to get a 5760 x 3240 px png file by right click save.

Please feel free to contact me if you have any inquiries.

Artwork by hasaqui, @hasaqui.
Made with p5js

metadata.name: This is the lie  #843
metadata.description:
The Project of the Nameless Sheep stems from an artistic and provocative necessity that aims to conceptually unite the Orwellian philosophy of 1984 with the thoughts of the great master Modigliani. The latter once stated, "I shall paint your eyes only when I know your soul."

The collection is a cry of disagreement towards destructive and uncontrollable globalization. It draws inspiration from an impersonal observation of modern society, critically examining historical events, corporations, and notable figures who have sold their soul for individualistic power that disregards the lives of others and the environment.

An ever-evolving project that will mature its search for soulless bodies over time.

1984 token, at a price as provocative as the theme of the collection.

Any reference to individuals, things or concepts is entirely coincidental and generated by a hash.
